Wachira, who served as police chief from 1996 to 1998, told the commission chaired by Justice Akilano Akiwumi that intelligence about impending attacks was hidden from him, as he painted a picture of rogue intelligence officers who seemed to enjoy protection from high up.Â The commission, which held public sittings between July 14 1998 and June 11 1999, laid bare correspondence between the police chief and CID bosses that exposed the dissatisfaction with security lapses.